This past weekend I watched the premier of the @ironmantri World Champs documentary on NBC along with the Emmy-nominated crew that’s like a triathlon family I’m so honored to be a part of. Inspiring to see everyone’s hard work & planning over the course of a year culminating in the 1st ever 2 day Kona, put together in a show about 80 minutes in length! The whole is greater than the sum of its parts, especially with the amazing stories of these athletes are told!

Shout out to super producers @sgodwinfilms @juliapolloreno @frlncr who made it all possible (and somehow edited the entire piece in 4 weeks! 🤯) And to my seal team @gregsworld who backed me up in the water and @connortrimble who assisted me in the air and the photo + video edit (including this little sizzle of my favorite clips) 

If you missed the live broadcast you can watch it on the @ironmantri YouTube channel, link in bio! 

The rest of the #ATEAM FILMERS AND FRIENDS include @rookmediaproductions @topho @itskennywithrow @rwbmultimedia @kurtisgefrom @jamesmitchell5 @wilhelmohman @jbolser1 @lauraospina92

pipeLINES - One of my favorite things about shooting with the drone is having a pulled back & raised up perspective that allows you to clearly see the swell lines coming in from deeper water. These lines or pulses of energy have always fascinated me and I find myself fixated trying to shoot the orderly way that they come to shore. I have so many shots highlighting this that I never really share, but here’s one that shows the second wave of the set with the third right behind it and the pack at Pipeline sandwiched between the two. #surfers #surfing #surfinglife #dji #mavic3cine #mavic3

MY WEBSITE IS LIVE!!! Super excited for my online print shop to be up and also as sustainable as possible! It was super important to me that I change my prints to being made + shipped in an eco-friendly way because I believe there needs to be a mind shift switch in consumerism and wanted my actions to speak for themselves. Hopefully others will see this and want to switch their prints or business to be as eco-friendly as possible🙌🏼 

With that being said, I wanted my first collection I launched online to be in line with this new vision and I came up with The Sustainable Beach House Collection which is a cohesive series of images that you can mix and match with tones + aesthetics that are complimentary of one another perfect to be shown solo, as pairs, or seamlessly fit in to any gallery wall. These pictures taken around the world reflect my love for the ocean and beach with the goal of transporting you to one of these beautiful tropical destinations. 

Check ‘em out and let me know what you think!!! Full portfolio coming soon 🤙🏽
#fineart #sustainable #sustainability #sustainableart #sustainableartist #surfing #surf #hawaii #artist #photographer #prints

It’s weird to identify as a photographer. 🤔 I started shooting photos a lot in 2014/15 while Instagram was blowing up when I was in college. This was before GoPro’s had screens, stories didn’t exist and you could only post 15 second horizontal videos haha. I haven’t shared a photo on Instagram in a year, but @instagram is a photo sharing app, or at least it was…. As I re-do my portfolio for my website and edit some of my favorites from the past few years I’ll be sharing them more frequently and I hope you enjoy the break from reels to check out a photograph for a change!

One of my all time new favorite photos I shot recently of @samschatz2 on a 1ft. day out with the @aquatech_imagingsolutions team in Waikiki. 

I am a wave snob. It’s really unfortunate to say, but with @surfline you check the cameras, you check the weather and if it’s not “perfect” a lot of times I don’t go out. I hate to admit it, but that’s just where it is for me when I feel like it’s better to spend my limited time on a computer. That sucks. I know it does and this session was a nice reminder that it doesn’t have to be perfect conditions, you don’t need all the big name pros out to have a fun time and capture great images.

This is a shot I’ve been trying to get for awhile without any hotels or people in it and usually when the conditions are good then there’s other photographers out or it’s just more crowded and it gave me the opportunity to get this epic, clean image with no people, no hotels, nothing except a skilled surfer on the nose and Diamondhead 🥹🙌🏼 

Shot with my @canonusa r5 & 24-70 at 35mm 🤙🏽

#aquatech_imagingsolutions #aquatech #waikiki #surf #surfers #surfing #surfline #surfersjournal #thesurfersjournal

The deadliest wildfire in the past 100 years in the U.S. tragically burnt much of the historic town of Lahaina to ashes. At this time there have been 114 lives reported lost with only 58% of the rubble being searched. Much of the touristic and economic hub of Lahaina, on the island’s western edge, was destroyed. A perfect storm of hurricane force winds mixed with drought and wild fire led to the deadly blazes. The fire spread at speeds up to one mile per minute, creating a dangerous inferno leaving those in the area little, to no time to escape. 

Today, on Oahu, many came together the morn in solidarity with a paddle out. Many on Oahu are closely connected to Lahaina whether it’s through friends, family or community. There have been donation drives and a lot of aid coming from Oahu to Maui to help those suffering.

Let the paddle out and community coming together inspire, and invigorate the next steps of healing, protection and rebuilding of Lahaina and her surrounding community struck by tragedy. Let us remember that this is a marathon, not a sprint and that there will be a lot of resources needed by the community to survive and rebuild. Please consider donating and supporting the West Maui community.

Shooting @ironmantri Women’s World Championships Tomorrow with @donaldmiralle and checking out some clips from last year🤘🏽 

Throughout college I shot for @hawaiiathletics and that’s where I really learned how to be a photographer. Unfortunately there aren’t many big professional events in Hawai’i aside from surfing, so it’s really exciting to be on Big Island again shooting this crazy race! It’s unlike anything else I shoot, there’s so much raw emotion involved. The sheer amount of training just to get here is amazing and then to swim 2.4mi, bike 112mi and then run a whole marathon 26.2mi is crazy! What people are going through is just wild to see as they truly push their body to the limit! 

#ironman #ironmantri #ironman #ironmanworldchampionship #ironmantraining #ironmanedit #ironmantriathlon #bigisland #hawaii

Ironman never ceasss to amaze me. It’s crazy shooting the finish line because you have to hold back getting choked up because you see how much emotion people are feeling from triumph, to pain, heart break and this release of adrenaline when they cross the finish line and it’s over. The determination these participants possess to push past limits their limits is really impressive. 

Here’s a few shots from this years @ironmantri helping shoot for @donaldmiralle the OG sports photographer from Iron Man, to Olympics and everything in between 🙌🏼 My goal this year was to shoot photos that weren’t like Dons which is hard to do because he’s “the man” as far as Iron Man photos go. It’s funny to see all of the other photographers emulate his style in Kona because he’s been so successful. But especially because I was shooting with him, I wanted to try and capture images he wasn’t getting or just get a little funky with it. I’m definitely happy with my shots, but maybe next year I’ll try to be more like Don again 😂😂😂🤘🏽 

The last slide is really rad, the last finisher came 17 minutes past when the race officially ended and the staff made a tunnel for her to come through, turned the music/mc on and cheered her in. It’s cheesy, but I love those feel good moments in sports 🙌🏼

And lastly, huge congrats to @lucycharles93 for the dominant win!!! I was rooting for her last year after going out so hard and she finished second, so stoked to see her come back and claim the title, especially after an injury. Check out the swimming slides to see how far ahead she was right out of the gate and she held that spot all damn day and set a course record!!!

Would’ve been a crazy make by @mikeybruneau // Currently I’m deep in to editing a massive short film and have all of my favorite clips from the past 9 years shooting on North Shore  in one place for the first time 😄🤘🏽 So psyched to put the film out and put out my favorite shots + some side edits from all of the footage! 

I am considering making a side edit for YouTube that’s something along the lines of “The Cutting Floor” or a mix of all of the top clips that didn’t make it in to the film. Let me know if you think I should, help give me that extra push haha 🙌🏼 One of the biggest things I struggle with editing is cutting out my favorite videos if they don’t drive the story forward. It feels heartbreaking, putting the time & effort (especially in the water, often times it’s extremely dangerous) in to shoot the clip, it lines up perfectly, you spent thousands on the gear to get it. All to end up not using it 😭 Maybe I romanticize the footage too much, or just genuinely love capturing beautiful moments. But this is actually a huge reason you, the rad person reading this on your phone right now, yeahhhh you haha, have not seen a lot of “new” content from me for the past 2-3 years. I realized my strength was on the planning or pre-production side of things & actually shooting vs. post production where I get bogged down editing, romanticizing the perfect creative outcome, but then it takes so long, I struggle to reach the end point. 

With that being said, I’m finally getting to the end point of this film that I have probably 4-500 hours in to at this point planning, producing, shooting and editing😅 & I can’t wait to share it!!! + all of the other clips I’ve unearthed along the way!

A happy accident // Even when you clean your housing as well as you can, sometimes sand and things shift around when you get in the water. That’s exactly what happened this day🤦🏽 I had a clean housing but on my swim out some sand landed and stuck right in the middle of my port. I knocked on my port, shook it and it wouldn’t budge…. The single grain of sand wasn’t an issue for any shots shooting at a more wide open aperture except when the light hit it perfectly for this one shot of @koarothman At first I was pissed knowing that one grain of sand “ruined” the shot. But the more I looked at it the more I liked it giving the photo a unique look. What do you think? Happy accident or tragedy? 😅

I’m thinking 2024 is the year to try a few more ideas I have with @johnny_the_ripper 🤘🏽
